{"id": 232061622, "title": "BTS\u2019 RM Notches His Fifth Solo No. 1 Hit In America", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin SEOUL, SOUTH KOREA - AUGUST 19: Rap Monster of BTS attends the BTS 1st Album \"Dark And Wild\" Show ... [+] Case\" at the Samsung Card Hall on August 19, 2014 in Seoul, South Korea. (Photo by Han Myung-Gu/WireImage) WireImage RM rules several Billboard charts this week, as his new full-length Right Place, Wrong Person and the tunes featured on his latest solo collection debut. He manages to hit No. 1 on both an albums and a songs tally this frame, as fans of the BTS star were quick to support the talent\u2019s latest release. One track from the album, \u201cNuts,\u201d gives RM another No. 1 in the U.S. The tune was a quick sales win\u2013which is common for members of BTS and the group itself\u2013and it brings the superstar back to the top spot on a ranking he\u2019s already ruled several times in the past. \u201cNuts\u201d launches at No. 1 on the World Digital Song Sales chart this week. The tally ranks the bestselling \u201cworld\u201d cuts in the country. In its first tracking frame, \u201cNuts\u201d sold 3,581 copies, according to Luminate. RM scores his fifth champion on the World Digital Song Sales tally this frame. He first topped the roster in 2020, when he joined Younha on her single \u201cWinter Flower,\u201d which became an instant leader. The following year, RM doubled his total count of solo No. 1s with \u201cDon\u2019t,\u201d which was fronted by eAeon. He then added two more No. 1s on the World Digital Song Sales list in 2022, which proved to be his biggest year on the ranking when looking at the summit. RM was one of five artists credited on the track \u201cSexy Nukim,\u201d which debuted atop the list. He was joined by Balming Tiger, Omega Sapien, BJ WNJN, and Mudd the Student on the smash. Before the end of that year, he and Youjeen reached the peak with \u201cWild Flower.\u201d MORE FOR YOU India-Pakistan T20 Clash In New York Today: Here\u2019s What To Know About The Biggest Cricket Game Of The Year A Ukrainian Drone Strike May Have Destroyed A Russian Air Force Su 57 Stealth Fighter Hit Man Mows Down Godzilla Minus One As Film Trends Big On Netflix \u201cNuts\u201d isn\u2019t RM\u2019s only new win on the purchase-only chart. In fact, the BTS powerhouse controls all of the highest three rungs on the tally this time around. RM\u2019s \u201cGroin\u201d launches in second place on the World Digital Song Sales list. Just behind that hit comes \u201cDomadachi,\u201d which features Little Simz. Thanks to his trio of new placements inside the top 10, RM has now scored 22 hits that have reached the region. As a soloist, he\u2019s sent a total of 25 tunes to the list, and almost all of them have cracked the highest tier. RM also manages to earn a No. 1 on one of Billboard\u2019s albums tallies. Right Place, Wrong Person opens atop the Top Rap Albums list, where it gives the singer\u2014and rapper\u2014his debut champion. ForbesBTS' RM Owns 60% Of A Billboard Chart This WeekBy Hugh McIntyre Hugh McIntyre Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "BTS singer RM earns his fifth No. 1 hit on Billboard's World Digital Song Sales chart this week as \"Nuts\" debuts in first place.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2024/06/09/bts-rm-notches-his-fifth-solo-no-1-hit-in-america/", "image": "https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/66638e5bf846afa71fb44f15/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&crop=2000,1500,x0,y67,safe&height=900&width=1600&fit=bounds", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:10:34", "author": "Hugh McIntyre,Senior Contributor", "authors": ["Hugh McIntyre", "Senior Contributor"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.078}